Question: How many companies have gross margin above 50%?
Actual_SQL_query: WITH gross_margin_calc AS (   SELECT      n.cik,     c.name,     (gp.val / rev.val) * 100 as gross_margin_pct   FROM 'data/s_and_p_500_parquet/num.parquet' gp   JOIN 'data/s_and_p_500_parquet/num.parquet' rev ON gp.cik = rev.cik AND gp.ddate = rev.ddate   JOIN 'data/s_and_p_500/comprehensive_companies.csv' c ON c.cik = gp.cik   WHERE gp.tag = 'GrossProfit' AND rev.tag = 'Revenues'     AND gp.qtrs = 0 AND rev.qtrs = 0     AND gp.val > 0 AND rev.val > 0 ) SELECT name, gross_margin_pct FROM gross_margin_calc ORDER BY gross_margin_pct DESC LIMIT 1

Question: Which Technology companies have shown declining ROE over the past 3 years despite revenue growth, and what are the underlying causes?
correct_answer:
{"format": "ROE decomposition analysis over 3 years", "visualization": "DuPont analysis charts showing ROE components", "sample_analysis": "WITH roe_analysis AS (
  SELECT c.name,
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM f.period_end_date) as year,
    AVG(f.revenues) / 1000000 as revenue_millions,
    AVG((f.net_income_loss * 4.0) / NULLIF(f.stockholders_equity, 0)) as roe,
    AVG(f.net_income_loss / NULLIF(f.revenues, 0)) as net_margin,
    AVG(f.revenues / NULLIF(f.assets, 0)) as asset_turnover
  FROM financials f
  JOIN companies c ON f.cik = c.cik
  WHERE c.gics_sector = 'Information Technology'
    AND c.name IN ('Meta Platforms Inc', 'Intel Corporation', 'Cisco Systems Inc', 'Oracle Corporation', 'Adobe Inc')
    AND f.period_end_date BETWEEN '2021-01-01' AND '2023-12-31'
    AND f.form_type IN ('10-K', '10-Q')
  GROUP BY c.name, EXTRACT(YEAR FROM f.period_end_date)
)
SELECT name, 
  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2021 THEN roe END) as roe_2021,
  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2023 THEN roe END) as roe_2023,
  ROUND((MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2023 THEN roe END) - MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2021 THEN roe END)) * 100, 1) as roe_change_pct
FROM roe_analysis
GROUP BY name

Question: Analyze the ROE sustainability for high-growth Technology companies over 7 years (2017-2023), distinguishing between organic growth and financial leverage effects.
correct_answer:
{"format": "ROE decomposition with growth sustainability analysis", "visualization": "Waterfall charts showing ROE drivers over time", "sample_analysis": "WITH roe_components AS (
  SELECT c.name,
    EXTRACT(YEAR FROM f.period_end_date) as year,
    AVG((f.net_income_loss * 4.0) / NULLIF(f.stockholders_equity, 0)) as roe,
    AVG(f.net_income_loss / NULLIF(f.revenues, 0)) as net_margin,
    AVG(f.revenues / NULLIF(f.assets, 0)) as asset_turnover,
    AVG(f.assets / NULLIF(f.stockholders_equity, 0)) as equity_multiplier
  FROM financials f
  JOIN companies c ON f.cik = c.cik
  WHERE c.gics_sector = 'Information Technology'
    AND c.name IN ('NVIDIA Corporation', 'Apple Inc', 'Microsoft Corporation', 'Alphabet Inc', 'Meta Platforms Inc', 'Tesla Inc', 'Adobe Inc', 'Salesforce Inc')
    AND f.period_end_date BETWEEN '2017-01-01' AND '2023-12-31'
    AND f.form_type IN ('10-K', '10-Q')
  GROUP BY c.name, EXTRACT(YEAR FROM f.period_end_date)
)
SELECT name,
  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2017 THEN roe END) as roe_2017,
  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2023 THEN roe END) as roe_2023,
  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2023 THEN net_margin END) - MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2017 THEN net_margin END) as margin_improvement
FROM roe_components
GROUP BY name
